messages.content:
Your template code is fine, but you’re running it with the wrong command.

### Why you get an `Untitled` file
If you use **“Templater: Create new note from template”**, Obsidian first creates a new note (often named *Untitled*) and then inserts the template into it. Your script then creates `posts/<slug>/index.md`, but the *Untitled* note remains—because Templater has no reason to delete it automatically.

### The correct ways to run it

#### Option A (recommended): keep using “Create new note…” but auto-delete the Untitled note
Use this version of the template (it detects the current temp file and deletes it after creating the real post):

```md
<%*
const tmpFile = tp.file.find_tfile(tp.file.path); // the file the template was inserted into

const title = await tp.system.prompt("Post title");
if (!title) { new Notice("No title provided."); return; }

const slug = title
  .toLowerCase()
  .trim()
  .replace(/['"]/g, "")
  .replace(/[^a-z0-9]+/g, "-")
  .replace(/^-+|-+$/g, "");

const base = `posts/${slug}`; // if vault is Hugo "content/" folder
// if vault is Hugo project root, use: const base = `content/posts/${slug}`;

const targetPath = `${base}/index.md`;

await app.vault.createFolder(base).catch(() => {});

if (app.vault.getAbstractFileByPath(targetPath)) {
  new Notice(`Post already exists: ${targetPath}`);
  return;
}

const safeTitle = title.replace(/"/g, '\\"');

const content = `---
title: "${safeTitle}"
date: ${tp.date.now("YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ss")}
draft: true
slug: "${slug}"
description: ""
tags: []
categories: []
---

Write a strong opening paragraph: topic + promise.

<!--more-->

## TL;DR
- 

## Outline
- 

## Draft
### 

## Notes / Sources
- 
`;

const file = await app.vault.create(targetPath, content);
await app.workspace.getLeaf(true).openFile(file);

// delete the temporary "Untitled" note that was created just to run the template
if (tmpFile && tmpFile.path !== file.path) {
  await app.vault.delete(tmpFile);
}

new Notice(`Created ${targetPath}`);
-%>
```

Now you can run **Templater: Create new note from template** and it won’t leave `Untitled` behind.

#### Option B: Don’t use “Create new note…”
Instead:
1) open any existing note (like a scratchpad/inbox note)
2) run **Templater: Insert template**
This won’t create an Untitled file at all. (But it *will* insert the script output into that note unless the template only runs inside `<%* ... %>` like yours—still, I prefer Option A.)

---

### One thing to confirm (path)
You said your vault is the Hugo **content folder**. If at the top of your vault you see `posts/`, then keep:
```js
const base = `posts/${slug}`;
```
If instead you see a `content/` directory at the top, switch to:
```js
const base = `content/posts/${slug}`;
```

Tell me which you see at the root of your Obsidian file explorer (`posts` directly, or `content/posts`), and I’ll give you the exact `base` line.
